# OPTIONAL — free-tier password protection.
#
# Netlify's one-click password screen needs a Pro plan. On the Free plan you
# can still gate the whole site with HTTP Basic Auth by renaming this file to
# "_headers" (no extension) and setting your own username/password below.
# Do this BEFORE sharing the link with anyone.
#
# /*
#   Basic-Auth: yourusername:areasonablystrongpassword
#
# You can list more than one username:password pair to give different people
# their own login (and revoke one later without changing everyone else's):
#
# /*
#   Basic-Auth: kate:choose-a-password
#   Basic-Auth: ed:choose-a-different-password
#
# Note: this file must live in the publish folder Vite builds to (the
# "public" folder here — Vite copies its contents into "dist" untouched).
